Half a dozen Bluepoint Oysters, a little gritty but very, very fresh.

Dr Gregory Hsu Board Certified Adult & Pediatric Eye Physician and Surgeon. Very polite, approachable and personable.

As usual, we over ordered. The Pork Tang-Suyuk will serve us well for tomorrow's lunch or dinner with fresh hot steamed Jasmine rice. Excellent service with plenty of banchan. Monday early lunch allowed us to avoid any sort of rush. Very pleased with the lunch experience.
Big bowl of sweet and sour sauce for dipping. Most of it went home with us.
Pork Tang-Suyuk was a big serving.  Sweet & Sour sauce is in a separate bowl for dipping. Looking forward to having it again tomorrow.

Mulbi Myeon is split bowl of two different styles of cold Korean buckwheat noodles. Yu-go likes to add mustard to the noodles in the clear broth.  And, white vinager to spicy red sauce noodles. He was ecstatic with his lunch choice.

If this is a small serving of Korean\/Hawaiian min & wonton, I can't imagine a big serving to share with two or three people.  Min was plenty to satisfy a most hungry person. MANDU as wonton were superb. Great value and quality.

Fried Mandu (Top Left); Kalbi, Meat Jun and  Chicken combo (Top Right); Spicy Noodle with oyster (Bottom Right); & Ox Tail plus clear bean noodles) ... Ox Tail needed more cooking time. Otherwise, every entree was filling and tasty.

The ox tail just needed more tender loving time on the stove.  So, we substituted with half and half cold noodle which is Yu-go's favorite.  Recommended by Russell's stepson for next time would be the beef short rib noodle soup. They didn't bill us for the ox tail noodle soup.
Damaged my wheel drum that had hit a curb. They were able to quickly repair and replace with a new tire within an hour. 5\/5 as far as I'm concerned.
Smaller Target. Grocery section in front. Restroom very clean. No stalkers wearing badges on the belt. Well stocked and neat. 3+\/5

Recent reviewers were most critical of cleanliness and service. Of course that prompted me to be on the deficiency lookout. The bad news is I didn't encounter such horrors. Everything tasted very fresh and tasty. Place was packed to the gills.
For just $9.16 before tax you cannot eat this good at a buffet. Drinks or beverages are a separate charge.
6 pc mixed half & half orginal and crispy chicken batter. Barely could finish eating them tasty juicy meaty pieces. Prefer the original batter.  Crispy is much too doughy and well done.

Since 2007, the Rose Regatta Dragon Boat Festival has held this event at LLV.  It brings public awareness to the forefront  about cancer and their survivors . Some of the Dragon Boat Clubs are exclusively cancer survivors. These clubs exist in many major metropolitans.

Hadn't had a chicken fried steak this good since Baja Beach Cafe. Score it an air tight 5\/5.

Prime rib medium rare for $8.99 with a purchase of a drink or beverage on any day of the week. Normally half of it goes home. Not thus time. It all went home in Yu-go 's belly. This tip ain't no bull. Perfect 5\/5.

Dried Orange Peel Beef. Last time I had such a quality experience was in San Francisco. Beef is corn starch coated and fried. Mixed in a sweet slightly tangy sticky Northern dark sauce with dried chili peppers. I would kill for this entree. Explosive 5+\/5 rating.
Ma Pau Tofu .... simply excellent with the soft fluffy fresh rice. No brained 5\/5 rating.

Best authentic Chinese food in all of Henderson. The Wu's purchased this restaurant four months ago and unfortunately tattooed by reviews of prior chop suey style references. Ignore those reviews and give this place a try. We were awe struck by the portions and quality of the Chinese food. We cannot at this time vouch for the Filipino, Thai or Combination  lunch plate specials. They are next on our list to try.

Hawaiian junkets brings thousands to Las Vegas.  Here's their flight schedule. Their passage includes all meals, hotel rooms plus air transportation. It's a heck of a deal.

Yu-go ordered the wide rice noodle spicy pork blood soup "Khao Soi" which was unbelievably satisfying. He's a big fan fan of Vietnamese "bun bo hue", but this soup experience erased any future desire for VN soups.
Their version of Vietnamese soup was incomparably superior to any pho I have ever tasted in this valley. I didn't come up for air until every drop of soup was cleaned off.
For later at home, their Pad Se Iw came up very short of expectation. Gai Lon extremely over cooked and total absence of "wok hay".

Mid-morning delight .... Tapioca Balls stuffed with seasoned ground pork, peanuts & sugar. Wrap in green leaf lettuce plus fresh sprigs of parsley.  Dip into sweet chilly dipping sauce. I dear say it's better than anywhere else in the Valley.
Remembering last night's bland Pad Se Iw,  Yu-go reheated the Chicken Pad Thai with extra fish sauce, sugar and Thai peppers. It turned out to be most tasty.  Extra two stars for my husband.

For the past three days,  Yu-go has been savoring his Thai Beef Jerky by eating just two pieces at room temperature per diem. He says it's the best he has ever eaten. Why ?  The seasoning is less soy sauce dominant and more sweet. The beef has a perfect portion of fat and it's not sliced but pulled. Most important ... not as dehydrated  and tough.
Up close photo of a baked Thai Dessert made of taro. coconut milk, sugar & eggs. This chiffon like cake is eaten slowly at room temperature. Goes really good with a cup of hot black coffee.
Thai Boat Noodle Soup !  Complete balanced meal in one bowl.  Beats going to Long Beach.
BBQ Pork Egg Noodle Soup !  Also includes meat balls. Only thing missing on the table is a bottle of red garlic vinegar. Hee hee ...

Nam Kao Tod !  Essentially a lettuce wrap fried rice appetizer with mint sour pork sausage . Very filling and could be considered a stand alone complete meal. Yu-go adds a couple of drops of Hoisin to sweeten the experience.
Sweet Basil Seed Honey drink  ... first time.  Refreshing and not over powering sweet. Basil seeds does embellish the overall experience.

Ready to go meal was purchased on Memorial Monday and consumed on Tuesday for lunch  by the two of us. Suggest cutting the meats and cucumber slices into smaller pieces.  Small cup of shrimp on the side.  Mix together before eating.  Excellent for taking onto flights. $8 meal you won't find anywhere else in the valley.
Drunken Noodle with Shrimp, the best we have ever had in the Valley!!
Duck Noodle, quack quack super delicious. Our third visit  in 8 days. The food here is irresistible!!
1st time taste of Palms Juice Coconut Nectar ... nice and refreshing. Perfection in a bottle.
Sister's Oriental Market Las Vegas NV grocery side
Restaurant half of Sisters Oriental Market. Established in 1990. It was a full house on this Tuesday afternoon.
Laos style papaya salad with raw black crab.  Medium was too hot for me. Next time I will order mild. Otherwise it is very good. Or one can order it Thai style which comes very mild.
Curry chicken was an excellent plate meal with rice.
Pork Pad Thai ordered medium was off the chart excellent.  Noodles are fresh and not dry reconstituted which is a significant difference.
Must visit at least once a week,  Pork Pad Woon Sen...Yu-go always add pepper vinegar for that spicy sour taste to this non spicy dish.
Beef salad, mild ..best we have ever had in this Valley!
Won't find these snacks at your local Ranch 99 or H Mart.
Khao Soi with a sample of tripe. Yu-go was dreaming about this all last night. And now, it's reality in his tummy. So good!
Thai Noodle Soup with wide rice noodle to change it up because I was jealous of Yu-go's .
9 inches of satisfaction ... sounds sexy eh ? Banh Mi for just $4.50
Wednesday Special ... Laotian  "Bahsoom" (sp) baked freshwater fish, fried sweet basil leaves, chili pepper and light oil dressing.    Yu-go went wild on this room temperature prepared dish.

Khao Poon changed my taste DNA forever more.  Amazingly adventuresome combination of crab, fish, ground pork, pig's blood, shrimp paste and lots of fresh veggies ... not to forget thin rice noodle.  Hypnotically enjoyable.
Cha Siu (BBQ pork) with wide rice noodles instead of the thin egg noodle.  You can customize your meal. Cannot beat the price or quality.
Look at what the postman just delivered ...  Sister's Oriental Market & Video yelp reviews averaged 4.7 stars. Congratulations are in order. They are truly the real deal.
Top:  Chicken Pad Thai with extra tamarind.  Bottom:  Simple chicken soup with flat rice noodles.  Don't be afraid to ask for specific seasoning to achieve  the ultimate flavor.
Rice noodles hand made by Sisters and included as part of this stirred fried Yu-go dish.
Pad Thai party tray ... terrific value.
Sister Dao ... a remarkable living story of making something from nothing ... and keeping a smile.
Chicken Rad Na .. that's gai lon and chicken, fermented yellow beans and wide style rice noodle.  It was a delicious  change from the usual dry to wet style of cooking.

Purchased the remaining four cherimoyas. Each fruit weighs approximately 1.25 lbs. They're not yet ripe enough to eat. Will  wait for them to soften. The four cost $41. Not exactly your everyday fruit in the produce section.  Also known as "custard apple".

Cherimoya is ripe for eating when it's soft to the palm. The skin is thinner than an avocado and cutting is effortless. Cut into quarters to facilitate scooping with a spoon. Must not eat the numerous black seeds .. poisonous if digested. The fragrance  is unforgettable perfumee. Membrane texture is  like a ripe pear and banana. Taste is a mixture of vanilla, pineapple, strawberry, mango with a minute faint bitter after taste. Unparalleled eating experience is addictive.
This a practice with dentists that all graduated from USC. They invest in their practice and have the latest equipment. Here is the machine that made my crown onsite.
Most recent Restaurant Grade was reported "A" July 2016 with 11 demerits.  That's 14 months ago. New ownership since. Will wait for new inspection before visiting.
Good news recent health department inspection on 9\/28\/17 found only 6 demerits to  earn an "A"  rating. Now in good conscience I can go and try the food.

We thought the dim sum quality and portions were excellent relative to two other premier dim sum houses.  And that is not including the much better service.  IMHO ... Changs is our favorite stop for dim sum.
Entire lunch including tea  charge plus tax for nine dishes came to less than $27.

Top: 12" Stagioni pizza; garlic bread; Sic Olives. Bottom: Wings garlic parm; Panna Cotta; Rack of Lamb med rare. After 17 years of absence, it tasted even better. Upholding Sicilian cucina perfection.

Lady luck was with us this Saturday fight night. We had made reservations and arrived 15 minutes early.  Waited five minutes and we were cordially seated. Plus, the UnitedWay parking lot was all ours.
Sorry to say ... dessert was better than the meal.
Was it as good as the first time ?   It did not take my breath away this 2nd go around.  Our good friend didn't know the difference.

Didn't realize the "Show in The Sky" last show was sometime in March 2013.  Several retailers on the mail floor had closed with brown wraping paper haphazardly taped to the windows. Non stop flights from Las Vegas to Montreal are Flights 1856, 1857 and 1858. Flight 1856 leaves in the AM,  LAS to YUL, 1857 is the return in the PM, YUL to LAS and 1858 is the redeye, LAS to YUL. Has not arrived or departed as scheduled.

Time to service our kitchen filter plus replace the softner's  leaky bypass valve.  The filter membrane did not need replacement which is $149. Overall, Ricardo was polite, timely  focused and a most competent technician relative to the prior Culligan technician. A five star performance.

Very relaxing atmosphere and comfortable seating.  All sorts of accolades on their walls. They even have their own brand of racy hot sauce .

Crunchy crisp seasoned Breaded Fried Prawn ... 8-9" in length.  Yu-go cuts into bite sized pieces to accommodate dipping into a dark mild vinaigrette sauce. Also on the plate course spicy semi-dry seafood paste. Most memorable tasting experience.

Cold Tofu introduces a soft moist cold experience and a definitive tasting recess from all the fried foods we had selected. Comes with fried dashi, finely julienned tender green onions plus lite japanese shoyu.

On the back side of the Yu-Yu menu are the skewered items. As novices we wanted to taste a few.  #61 Pork Filet, #73 Curry Beef Tongue & #82 Octopus Leg (tentacle). Each item was very distinct in taste & texture. Dipping sauce takes experience to another level. Looking forward to trying other back page items.
$9.50 vinaigrette Sashimi Salad was a standalone complete meal. Fish was in small cubes. Complimented well with all our fried foods.

If you're into fried chicken, then Fried Jidori (chicken) is a must order. May also order as a one piece skewered with choice of white or dark meat. Wish my Karrage experiences at Ramen restaurants were as good as this Fried Jidori.

I've had Yu-Yu bookmarked for the longest time. So glad I decided to pluck the oldest bookmarks first. This style of dining allows for the maximum choices without over eating or wasting. A near perfect Japanese meal. IMHO.

I've been dealing with this dealership's service department for eleven consecutive years. After making an appointment for my vehicle's annual emission test and oil change, the service manager called and notified me of a need for a transmission flush and a brake job. I said I would have to think about the brake job, but he may proceed with the emission test, oil change and transmission flush. I called back and told the service manager that I would seek a second opinion. Read next tip.

Cut to the chase, service manager tells me now that they can't do the emission test but could have it done elsewhere with an up charge. "What ?" I said. "You should have that up charge waived." He tells me it takes at least an hour to discuss this matter with supervision. Next tip ...

I'm now finished with breakfast. I drove back to the dealership to pay for my oil change and transmission flush. Not seeing the service manager eventhough the cashier had to retrieve the work order and invoice through him. Drove my car to the Terrible's Chevron Station on Boulder at Trails Shopping Center had my emissions test completed and paid for within ten minutes upon arrival. Two hours later, service manager calls me to bring my car back for an emissions test. Their equipment works again.

I told the service manager I had already had my emissions test completed and certified elsewhere.  What I didn't tell him was my   dissatisfaction and insult I had taken as if I had just fallen off a truck heading for a slaughter house. How stupid do you think I am?

Yu'-go's treatment is a routine injection to the same eye every other month.  No matter how many times, its always painful to observe the procedure.
Yu-go here to see Meher Yepremyan M.D. by referral of Dr. Gregory Hsu, Opthamologist
Scallops peaked with uni ... excellent !  Sea otter's delight too. LoL
Special Sapporo Ramen (Ramen Sora owns this restaurant too) chewy and curly ... a personal favorite style. Broth was excellent !
Spring Mix Ohitashi boiled and re-boiled spinach with benito flakes. Enjoyable and our only vegetable for this super late Yakatori dinner.
Chicken Thigh with Citron Peppers ... mild bite along with perfect crunchy chewy moist experience.

Oysters were extremely fresh. Mild vingarette applied to each. Slurping good ... !

Only a couple items I wouldn't order again. Being that it was near midnight and not over runned by diners, our table service was excellent. Ambiance and quiet was most appreciated following a enduring 2,500 mile flight home.
HACHI" means good fortune in Japanese.
Root beer float with two scoops of vanilla ice cream. All soda beverages are bottled. No fountain drinks like at Costco. 5\/5 stars for great taste and memories.
Carolina slaw dog filled with coleslaw, pulled pork, watermelon rind BBQ sauce, diced onions with additional .99 for tots with the dog. Totally 5\/5 for flavor and portion

Banchan skimpy ... nice occidental touch
Ordered beef brisket, spicy pork bulgogi, smoked pork belly, Cajun shrimp
Salad,  Agedashi tofu, KFC, japchae
Seasame chicken ... fried chicken breast
Mix feelings for my initial visit. $38 tax & tips  Not inspired to try again..
Came for the 4th of July holiday buffet@ $12.99\/pp. The cooked vegetables were quite good, the goat curry was excellent. As for the chicken both over cooked and under seasoned.
Another mural ... dining area is cool, clean and with an open ambiance.  No odor of the foods.

Just a one time sampling of each item from the buffet . Cooked veggies were pretty good. Curry lamb most tasty. Chicken anything  was well done and under seasoned

Is Pure Indian the best Indian buffet east of the Strip ?  Furthest from the worst,  but certainly not the very best. BTW ... the restaurant is soundproof from the airport traffic.

We hadn't seen the owner in over thirteen years.  Amazingly, he remembered us.
Not open until 5pm this Sunday. That sucks!

Sunday 5\/21\/17 Is this the beginning of the end? Drove all the way across the valley to find the restaurant closed without any signage indicating changing of operating hours. Our bad we should have called and read the reviews and tips. The sporadic closing is obviously a problem. Highly doubt I will go out of my way to come back. Update 5\/22\/17 checked the website new hours now posted. Closed Sunday's. Mon-Sat...11:30 am to 2:30 pm. Reopens on Fri-Sat 5:00 pm - 10:00 pm. Only open 25 hrs a week.
Pear & Pomegranate & Burrata salad prepared with roasted pears, petit greens, burrata, carmelized pecans and pomegranate vinaigrette.  Unforgettable  salad 5+\/5
Truffle fries. Ordered extra crispy. Added salt and pepper to take it up a notch. 5\/5
Smoked salmon served on a house made pretzel roll and all the fixings that would MORE  than satisfy a smoked salmon lover. 5 smokin' fingers approval!!
Opened since 9\/11. Greeted right away and offered complimentary fresh squeezed Mandarin orange juice
Milk Tea ... Froggylicious yummy !
Twice cooked chicken wings were borderline soy sauce style. I could take or leave them... more likely the latter.

Hainan free range chicken may be exclusively Flock & Fowl in this valley. So I give it a 5-\/5. Not quite like Singapore or Portland's Nong's Khao Man Gai where they offer a choice of dark or white meat.
Hawaiian Style Saimin. Char siu, scrambled egg, fish cake & green onion. 5+\/5 perfection !
Mixed Plate:  Furikake chicken and Kalua Pig with cabbage seasoned with Hawaiian salt. Enough food to feed two. "BROKE YOUR MOUTH ONO !"  Easy to score 5+\/5.

Surrounded .... with hot stuff

Little too early.  KAU KAU stop before flight to Orlando.
10:10 am & it's already full of diners. Yes, the food is that good.
Said now includes wonton too. Only $7 top !
Hamburger steak saturated with gravy plus two scoops of fresh rice.  Broke your mouth.
Huli Huli Chicken with 2 scoops of rice plus mac salad . Ono delish ! Can substitute rice for fries or brown rice. Also, mac salad for green salad. Always happy happy !
Saimin ... complete meal.
Inari Sushi ... to go ! Taste later.

We've been patronizing this 808 restaurant for many months. Today was a true disappointment.  Never encountered shoyu chicken in brown-ginger root gravy and fried chicken encrusted with sweet batter. Plus chicken parts were ultra small.  Mac Salad continues to be too salty.  I think it's time to try somewhere else.
There is no signage to the restaurant. It is across from American Shooters and next door to a business called Sonagi which looks vacated.
Again, no signage but if you see this Japanese screen door, you have come to the right place.
Sushi counter seats ten. GEN (owner) is the one in the middle
Sat at the sushi counter flanked by two very nice well traveled foodie couples. Yu-go and I shared the following Omakase Dinner Courses: Gen's Premium & Nigiri plus a Uchihwa-ebi "Samurai Lobster
CHEF'S TABLE @ Yui menu ... opened December 7th
Chef & Owner Gen (opening chef @ Kabuto) now brings unabashed sushi perfection to Yui. Just remember that an evening here may alter your sushi expectations forever.
It's about time the Eastside of Las Vegas gets its own full service Asian market. This changes our shopping pattern big time!
You can get a list of what is being served by the cash register @ Asian Kitchen  Especially for their party trays.
Constantly busy. There are plenty of tables to dine in.

This three item combo plus chow mein cost $8.11 includes the sales tax. Black pepper pork chops, crispy fried chicken with sauce, honey spice chicken plus a choice of rice or chow mein. 4+\/5 rating for the meats.  Chow mein was a 3-\/5. There was more than enough to feed both of us.
Some Bread Farm desserts from their bakery. Typical Chinese baked goods. Realize it's new. Give them time to improve. Otherwise it's very good. 4+\/5.
During grand opening, the store is obviously overstaffed and comprised mainly of Latinos and Filipinos. While checking out, be sure to ask for shopping rewards card and any other discounts.
Noodles and pork adobe was most disappointing 1\/5 So bad we threw it out.

BBQ combo of Lechon Kawali, Soy Sauce Chicken and Roasted Duck with garlic rice. It includes a tall soft drink. Mix bang of results. Roasted Duck 4-\/5, Soy Sauce Chicken 3\/5 and Lechon Kawali 1\/5. Garlic Rice was the best item of the BBQ combo.
Cream Wafers on sale !
This use to be Mia Bella Salon
Soup, rice & dessert were comped ! Excellent table service. Meal was more of a roller coaster experience. Wanted a grand Chinese meal so badly following our return from Ottawa.
Half order Boiled Chicken with minced ginger .... tough & dry !  Never experienced this before.  Zero dark meat too. Caused us to pause & stop eating.
Pea Pod with fresh garlic was very much over cooked and mushy. So disappointing.
Seafood Claypot was plentiful and pretty good. Would order again.
Half shell oysters with black bean sauce.  Would order this again.
Popular place filled with Chinese diners. Maybe the next time we should just stick only with the seafood.

Came here to satisfy a friend's wishes for a Boba drink. Ordered saimin & cake noodle with grilled chicken. Saimin noodles were the textbook example of assuming the customer is too dumb to notice the differences of real thing and their con job.

My two friends shared an order of noodle cake & grilled chicken ... Hawaiian style. Yu-go also shared an order of the same. Without the cornstarch soy sauce gravy, the eating experience would had been terribly dry and tasteless. However there's a price to be paid ... the ugly dry mouth syndrome.

As for the smell, it's greasy drain pipes that need professional attention.  Btw, the smell discouraged our friends from ordering their Boba drinks. It was the good intentions that pointed us here ... too bad Boba Hut didn't match their yelp 4+ star hype. This is close to being one of our worst eating experiences in the 20 years of living in this valley.

After shopping for chinese greens from next door, I had to order a half pound of  Crispy Bagnet.  I requested skin and fat.  Less meat better tasting. IMHO. Got home and sampled a piece.  Wow ... Fragrance, texture and taste was unbelievably enticing.  Little plum sauce for dipping will take matters to the next higher level.   LoL
The young man behind the counter was so helpful ... he deserved a tip. Of course it pays to be nice to him too.  LoL
Carne asada nachos ... enough to feed two to three. Great value with heaping portions. If you're super hungry, it fits the bill.
Thursday Special ... bean tostada, cheese enchilada, more beans and rice for $6.50. Does not include bl beverage.  Hearty and tasty meal.
Felipito's reminds me a lot of another popular Mexican grill on College that I use to frequent for many years and unfortunately ceased visiting.
Felipito's is open 24\/7. That's a big time plus for me.
Crazy Combo , 3 beef rolled tacos with rice and beans
Friday daily special, fish tacos with rice and beans
Beautiful menu designed for easy ordering. Plenty of pictures for reference.
Guess Guess Shrimp" served on an aluminum foil daisy.  Astonishing presentation matched by the entr√©e's southwest China's regional renowned spices.
Baby Bok Choy was a substitute. Orginally wanted to order Alarn Lettuce but not available this Friday evening. Skillfully prepared with garlic. IMO, an expensive alternate.
Toothpick Lamb with Cumin" a very popular entr√©e ordered by practically every table. The spice Cumin is an acquired taste and best matched on lamb.
Started out with "Marinated Pig''s Feet".  A Yu-go must have. Not spicy but cooked to perfection where the tenderness of ligaments, tendons and skin delivered total enlightenment.
I've been to Chengdu to visit the Panda Center. The strengh of the seasoning there is much more potent than this evening's experience.
Chengdu Taste #1 is in Honolulu HI on Sheridan just few blocks south of King Street.

Follow the arrows on the floor mats to the ordering station. Bring the sales ticket to the cashier and they'll collect your money.  Find a table and one of the cashiers will bring your food to you. You can bus your tray or just walk away and let some else deal with your mess.
Dry rubbed baby back ribs and brisket were extremely well done and served at room temperature.  Chicken was hot, plump and juicy. Luved the fried okra and BBQ beans.
I've had BBQ experiences in Portland, Kansas City, Memphis, Houston, San Francisco & Las Vegas.  If you prefer dry rubbed super well done and well trimmed meats ... this is your BBQ hangout.
Ordered the three meat combo with two sides. The pork ribs are an additional $5 surcharge. That wasn't disclosed until we got to the cashier. The combo is plenty to feed both of us.
Chicken Fried Steak topped with Chipotle Sausage gravy, two eggs & breakfast potatoes mixed with seasoned onions. Not spicy and perfect portions to carry one over till dinner time.

Yu-go hadn't ordered a Monte Cristo since his PDX days which was two plus years ago. Rather than a dipping container of jam, it's crafted as tear drops on the plate. Not buttery greasy and deceptively filling. White cheese is mild (not sharp) and the ham is lean, tender and not salty. Most satisfying.
Dialed their phone # @ 10:15 am.  NO ANSWER ...  just generic vm. Are they out of business ?

Had two more dim sum dishes than their competitor on Sahara, and my total bill was several dollars less. The only disappointment was their har gaw's rice noodle skin was over steamed. Dim sum is larger than their competitor on Sahara.  Noise level is higher here.  No physical changes or improvements by new operators.

HK Garden participates in the "Yelp Cash Back" program.  However they charge 3.5% extra for payments by credit card. Just raise the prices and be done with the credit card surcharge. Even then they are still less expensive than their competition on Sahara. The new operators did little to none in enhancing the ambiance...
Roy Ellamar & Momo B.
Yu-go B., Roy Ellamar & Momo B.  We go back a few years.
Slight physical changes to bar & front exterior. All new and most comfortable furniture
A few new pieces of kitchen equipment for roasting meats and poultry.
Snack Wagon Delight ... just $8 per selection.  Only thing missing is the dim sum lol.
Smoked Trout with black sesame crackers . Seasoning includes wasabi creme fraiche. It was so good I could snack on it all day.  Nice starter!
Steak tartare seasoned Thai style spicy raw beef with lime, cilantro,  and chili. Eat it like a taco using the red cabbage leaves or chard. Finger lickin' good!
Flat Bread topped with roast pork, smoked ham, apricots and Drake goat cheese. Decivingly filling.
Sashimi of the day, fresh ahi tuna seasoned with bourbon soy sauce and micro wasabi on bed of seaweed salad. Sushi lover's will not want to share.
Rock Shrimp Tempura seasoned with spicy aioli, pickle daikon and furikake. Have to be careful to not inhale it. Better yet, don't share this dish with anyone.
Roasted octopus served with preserved lemon, Weiser potatoes and sea asparagus. Gives Greek  and Japanese  restaurants a run for their money!
Alaskan Halibut served with artichokes, snap peas, baby carrots and spinach veloute. A fish lovers must have. DO NOT EAT HALIBUT ANYWHERE ELSE!!
Sampler platter of meats: Lamb Chops, Culotte Steak and Foie Gras. MEAT LOVERS DREAM PLATE! !
Scalloped Potatoes. Cheesy good.
Saut√©ed Spinach. Got to have something green with this amazing dinner. lol
Sweet Wagon Delights. Any 3 items but the cupcakes for just $10 bucks. Cupcakes are $4.50 each.
Peach Cobbler with Cherry Bourbon Ice Cream. I walked around the restaurant to make more room. And I am glad I did.
Made another reservation for my anniversary and birthday.
Roasted Green Tea Ice Cream was the finale dessert.  Wow !  What a fantastic dinner.
Wagyu plus minty soba with uni and lobster bits. Wagyu comes with certification. Best for last.
Uni from Hokkaido ... plus more nigiri zushi.   Heavenly delicious
Nigiri zushi

Miso soup with manila clams and lobster plus nigiri zushi
Shanghai Hairy Crab (Hong Kong   could not sell this year) plus Chawan Mushi ... Wow again and again.

Pickled cucumbers ... refreshingly good !
Beef pancake ...very tasty, slightly chewy dough, beef filler is well seasoned ... delicious!
Steamed shrimp, pork & squash dumplings ... yummy !  Comes with sweet light vinaigrette dipping sauce.

Kare Kare and Pork Adobo combo

Located behind Auto Zone
Monster box with Spicy Pork Roll and 4 pcs sushi, seaweed salad, egg, goroke. Great value for the money.
Chicken Wing box served with combination brown and white rice, seawood salad, egg, goroke. Wings could be a little spicer, otherwise ate everything no leftovers tonight.
Party platter for 2.. 36 pcs ..8 pieces dragon roll, 3 regular rolls x 6 pcs (18pcs)  and 10 pcs sushi
BOWL" 1\/2 lb. fish on top of salad or rice. Choose salad. Oh wow !  Excellent choice on the first day of summer.
#1 Party Platter, Red Dragon Roll and Basic Rolls of Spicy Crab, Salmon Skin and California roll. 10 pieces of assorted  Nigiri. I' m hungry and it tastes really good!

Waited seven weeks for both our haircuts. When it comes to styling Asian hair, no one is better.
It's been a long time since our last visit to a L & L. (Stephanie)

Mix Plate ... enough to feed both of us. Includes Kalbi, chicken, beef plus Japanese sticky rice and macaroni salad.  Pretty tasty and most filling.  Requested sauces on the side.
Chicken Katsu Curry with Malay style mild spiced yellow curry. They also have tonkatsu sauce in plastic tubs at the counter.  Expertly fried for crunchy crispy moist bite. Excellent value too.
Ahead of 2017 Federal regulations,  menu discloses calories consumed ... anybody who dines here is more than likely to totally ignore those calorie numbers.  LoL
Ordered just one bbq mix plate which feeds both of us.
Momo finding hard to restrain herself from devouring her food!
Three Meat combo includes choice of diced, Mac salad plus refillable fountain drink ... all for less than $10. Break your mouth deal.
Been a year since last visit. Chicken katsu with Malay Yellow mild spicy curry.  Killer meal.  Choice of rices, Mac salad plus fountain drink. Would easily satisfy two average appetites.

Next door to Friendly Donuts is the only thing in common.  The mixed plate was simply awful in quality of meats and preparation.  IMHO, this franchise has lost sight of the fact that they are feeding human beings. Only thing I could do was throw the entire meal away.  I know the truth hurts. One star attempted murder of my appetite.
Complimentary starter is a bread board served with sweet whipped butter (5\/5)
Chilled yellow and red beets with a milk yogurt that masked the slight bitterness of the red beets. Great way to begin our dinner (5\/5)
Chicken Parmesan much larger than normal serving with an undistinguished marinara sauce (3.9\/5)
Paparadelle Bolognese, the pasta is normally chewy, but not in this case. The sauce required chili flakes to give it more character\/flavor.  (3.97\/5)
Carbonara Mac and cheese. Was better than the Paparadelle. (4.4\/5)

Appetizer "Involtini di Michelle" ... yes ... fried puffed veggie lumpia (egg rolls with no egg) with basil & cilantro & butter leaf lettuce wrap. Served with a sweet chili and Wasabi aioli that we didn't even use.

Appetizer "Bocconcini D'Agnello in Padella" Grilled marinated baby lamb chops on a sizzling platters served with dates. Includes a mild, zesty Sriracha (Left) and a yang Wasabi (Right) dipping sauces. This dish is  "A LAMB LOVERS MUST HAVE" !!!!! (6\/5)
Linguine Alla Mediterranea" rock shrimps, bay scallops, baby asparagus, brown butter, sage and the distinguished feature, none other than Chef Rudy's white truffle oil !  Fantastico !!!
Romanesque "Specialita' Della Puglia" Rigatoni pasta, mushrooms, peas, prosciutto, garlic in cream sauce. Talk about taking it all to the next level of excellence !!
I've already made arrangements to have dinner again on Thursday. Charismatic principal Chef Rudy "Valentino " Janeo Jr's cucina produces the ultimate mangia experience.

Thursday evening visit: Mountain sized tender Osso Bucco overlooking a deep meadow of paparadelle to absorb the rich flavored Chef Rudy's Soubious sauce. It's quite overwhelming at first glance. Serious cucina stuff for serious diners.

Thursday must be pasta day ... just teasing.  But, don't take for granted Chef Rudy's Osso Bucco sauce without understanding his life long passion for Italiano pasta cuisines. This spaghetti dish is a bullseye.

Ordered twins ... two thick trimmed premium bone-in ribeye steaks that had been marinated over night. Romulus and Remus would had remained in peace for eternity after such a gastronomic meat lovers' meal. The truffle oil mac and cheese takes second to none at the Coliseum. We could only twinkle are eyes and say "wow!" after the first taste.
Sunday Lunch:  Greek Salad split into two servings
Sunday Lunch:  Chef Rudy's "Concoction" (not a menu item) of chicken breast, pepperoccinis, red peppers, lettuce as a sandwich with a jalape√±o cream spread. Molto Bene !!
Sunday Lunch: Another Chef Rudy's Sicilian pasta dish, Traditional Sicilian Carbonara, will be part of the new menu. Molto Buona !!
Sunday Lunch: Sugared Crispy Won Ton Skins, topped with vanilla ice cream, fresh strawberries,  carmelized dates and whipped cream. Magnifico!
Thursday night ... another beautiful dinner.
Linguine vongole ... clams galore with plenty of precious creamy garlicly white sauce to douse the slightly near perfect aldenti noodles. Not perfect but very very close.
Calamari & Onion Ring Fritti ... three dipping sauces:  marinara, Sriracha & Wasabi aioli. You pick cause they are all good.
Italian tart ... simple and smooth and deadly delicious.
There is perfect reason why I have dined here four times in the past twelve days. The food is absolutely fantastic and it makes me most happy.
Late night Friday dinner of lamb chops, lumpia plus mushrooms risotto to pack your belly with a smile.
EGG PLANT for lunch ... the perfect way
Special Request Linguini Vongole with a touch of fermented black beans ... for lunch.  Thank you Chef Rudy Janeo for sending my taste buds to the moon.
We will be here for this Premier Wine Dinner.Show. Chef Rudy doesn't do anything half way!

60 diners attended Chef Rudy's "Wine Dinner Show". Each course included an Italian wine pairing. Stuffed jumbo shrimp with crab meat & frisee salad with apple wood bacon dressing paired with Allegrini Solosola Vermentino (pear & apricot). Wow !!!
Roasted NY Strip loin topped with thyme aioli glaze accompanied with scalloped potatoes, green beans. Paired with Brancaia Chianti (blackberry, cherry and a touch of almond). Another  Wow !!!
Limoncello with berries, paired with Rondo Prosecco. Wow !!!
Eat with your hands, Bruschetta calamari appetizer ... zesty and tender.  Stay tuned for an upcoming n√©w menu that will feature this tasty goodie.
Chicken Prosciutto, tender salty Italiano prosciutto and chicken, kalamata olives and artichokes served with pasta sauteed in home made marinara sauce for total satisfaction with a big smile.
Linguine Fra Diavolo served with jumbo shrimp. Wakes you up and opens your sinuses. Like amore for the first time!

To cleanse our palette ... Sweet Limoncello ! (to be part of upcoming Chef Janeo's new menu) Do I need to say more for this beautiful Sunday night dinner with Geno playing his velvety romantico electric guitar music.
Chicken Prosciutto, tasty  prosciutto and chicken, kalamata olives and artichoke hearts, served with marinara sauce, puts a smile on your face.
Chicken Piccata ... enormous serving.  Plenty of capers to make it special. Includes a heavy portion of linguini.  This past Saturday we were taking part in celebrating a good friend's birthday.
Free champagne for all ladies ... read Chef Rudy's announcement ... every Thursday evening and into the wee night.
Yes ... send cash gifts to momo b. in care of Chef Rudy Janeo. Will donate and personally match dollar for dollar all proceeds collected to breastcancer fundraiser in October.
Bruschetta shrimp with a wake me up spicy kick. New fall menu item. A must have starter.
Della Puglia ... heart and soul entree.  Next time will request a little more of Chef Rudy's magic creamy sauce ... that sounds so sexy !
Caprese Salad with Burratta.  Whack me on my head and take me home to papa. So... good !
Start of Wednesday evening as we leave from our home for Il Chianti Italian. No rain in those clouds above.
Chef Rudy's brand new Fall Menu starting Thursday September 8th. Old favorites plu new entrees to tease your taste buds.
Chef Rudy Janeo's presents his new and bigger Fall Menu starting this Thursday.
We have the whole restaurant to ourselves listening to Musica de Italiano .

Sunday late lunch splitting our Insalata Classica plus Spaghetti Bolognese topped with a side order of roasted Italian sausage each. Photo represents half order. Chili flakes to take it over the edge.
September Wine Paired Prix Fixe Dinner. Wednesday 21st. We attended last month's dinner. Talk about a fantastic dining experience.
Our first try of Chef Rudy's lasagna. And, it will consume you with its richness and texture that will make forget everything else around you.
Special request for linguini with just olive oil and fresh garlic topped with fried Italian style breaded calamari. Unassuming and delicious.
Jeno will begin playing his guitar this Thursday evening.  So now you can hear his beautiful guitar music from Thursday through Sunday evenings. (Thursday & Sunday evenings are less crowded)
One of Chef Rodolfo's signature dishes is the Lynn Pear with Cheese Tortellini and shrimp. Chef's very proud of this speciality because no one else can even come close to replicating it.
Jeno makes romantic tunes with his guitar Thursday thru Sunday evenings.
Chef Rudy's place is packed tonight!

Fettuccine alla Funghi ... tomato vodka sauce ... lots of shrimp & scallops, Porcini mushrooms & asparagus ... one order feeds two. Of course we had lamb chops as an appetizer.  Still the best in the valley !
German Apple Strudel ala mode ... new dessert offering not on menu. Raisins & nuts. Pastry is flaky not puffy.

Purposely held off returning to visit Chef Rudy until month end and after 8:30 pm. He told us reservations only during our five month absence. That busy ! This evening, Chef Rudy allows us to sample a new appetizer deep fried rice balls.  Very refined and unique with perhaps a bit too much of a garlic presence as a starter dish.
Yu-go's extra meatball dominates his spaghetti Bolognese.  Exceptional portion and value.
When making reservations, do yourself a favor by requesting Roger to be your server.
My half of Wednesday Special Bone-in Rib Steak with Cheese Wheel Pasta Carbonara.  Brilliantly prepared and perfect portion.
Just about ready to be delivered by Chef Rudy himself
Chef Rudy meticulously blended the freshly melted cheese into the pasta carbonara. He's well aware that Yu-go is taking photos of him. Hence the big Manila smile!
Salty Caramel Gelato

Just one of the  new dishes included in the new menu.

Joining hundreds of diners for #Vegas Strong fund raiser on this Monday evening only.

The bar here is the highest.  In a couple hours,  i shall taste and judge.

Restaurant staff experience and attention to detail is very prevalent.  Not super fancy but certainly comfort in mind.  Food is perfectly seasoned for an authentic Korean cuisine experience.
Ono Plate for me !  I'm very hungry too.
Yu-go's Korean Fried Chicken Sandwich... with fried potato nuggets. ... So delish too.
For pick ups and deliveries
Chicken & Basil with 3 Special Sauce. Not spicy but very flavorful   First time trying.
Sizzling Rice Soup with Seafood. Broth wasn't hot ... pretty silent presentation.
Green Onion Pancake is a must !
Pork Stuffed Pocket Bread ... under seasoned for Yu-go, but still enjoyable.
Stir fried Taiwanese lettuce aka  A-Choy ... a dinner favorite.
Taiwanese Sausage ... good but wouldn't order again. Little over valued.
Choose Buddha Bowl aka spicy tuna with extra scoop of fish over lettuce.  Order the large bowl and save 1 or 2 bits.

Very late lunch and didn't want to spoil my dinner. BUDDHA BOWL with extra scoop of spicy tuna was perfect to keep us going till next meal. Found the tuna poke to be unsually gristly along with unpleasant fishy smell even though masked with dressing and seasoning.
Lechon Kawali, Bangus with mango salsa salad plus comped ube pancake. Big portions and very Filipino !  Great atmosphere.

The ube pancake was the hit. Rather disappointed with the less than crispy Lechon Kawali and very over cooked Bangus. Once three large groups showed up, the service quality was all over the place in a negative sense.
Chirashi comes with miso soup and small salad
Chirashi over a bed of rice was incredible (5\/5). Excellent value.
Chirachi condiments
It's Friday and it's also curry day for the entire Japanese Navy. Ample curry potato\/veggie portion to eat with rice and pork tonkatsu.  (4.3\/5)

Served separately the pork tonkatsu is satisfying but not memorable. Yet it is better than several other respected westside curry restaurants. Everybody has a varied expectation of curry. We prefer spicy and topped with pickled radish. Not delivered in such a manner here.
Omakase ($69) choice of Yuzu Sorbet or Green Tea Cheese Cake. Very refreshing and distinctly mild flavored sorbet.
Omakase ($69) Sushi
Omakase ($69) sushi
Omakase ($69) cooked salmon with agedashi broth ... got to remember to slow down
Omakase ($69) sashimi plate. Variety of fish changes daly
Omakase ($69) tempura ... perfectly fried ... didn't share with Yu-go. LoL
Omakase ($69) Zen-Sai halibut sashimi salad with truffle oil and ponzu sauce ... this was the beginning plate of my Omakase dinner.  Tremendous value and quality.
Our two other guests shared a mochi dessert. Flavors mango, red bean and green tea.
Yu-go ordered the sashimi plate ... he was certainly most happy.
Our friends ordered Mermaid Roll (photo), dinner chirashi, dark premium maguro sushi Ala carte.

Wednesday night get together with another yelp couple. One of them an avid fish eater and the other a sea captain. The expectations were very high. Hiro and his staff amazingly hit the bullseye in every which way. Two hours of pure enjoyment and great memories. Arrigato Hiro !
Friday late lunch ... Yu-go's favorite Sashimi that includes salad.  Under $20.
I love their bento box and Yu-go loves their sashimi lunch. Between the two meals there is plenty to share. Our server Jenny always remembers Momo.
Bento lunch never again. Dry or overcooked.
Chirashi was ultra fresh ! Very enjoyable.
Omakase ends with a choice of dessert. The last piece of sushi served was a creamy Santa Barbara uni.
Premium cut zushi
Black cod was served with a sweet mustard and more zushi
Sashimi platter, Oyster, quail egg and uni shooter, organic cold tofu with soy dipping sauce and garnish. All very impressive.
Tuna belly tartar on crispy rice, Shrimp and vegetable tempura and halibut with onions, cilantro in a light vinegarette broth.
Starter, Halibut from Korea in truffle oil and Chef Hiro san.

If you have never tried an Omakase I would highly recommend this one at Sushi Hiro it is a great value for less than $100.00. Go early because you will receive undivided attention of Sushi Master Chef Hiro.
Friday night it is packed. Ordered the pork combo, did a check in and a tip and received a Pork Skirt meat as a bonus. Nancy our server advised us of this.
Dessert ... mellow cheesecake cubes to counterbalance the barrage of fresh garlic, sweet pungent Korean marinades on their fresh cut meats, ultra quality ban chans, and trail blazing dipping sauces.

Lucky #88 on a late Friday night. Between 5 pm and 9 pm, it was like Pork Chop Hill under siege by waves of diners. We walked right in at aproximately 10 pm and were seated before we could fully absorb the magnitude of the size of the restaurant. Table service was exceptionally fluid, responsive and authentic.
Spicy pork skirt meat was our Yelp reward for our check-in and tip made on site. They do verify the your comments. Btw, the side dish was excellent tasting.

Pork shoulder meat is slowly cooked over the flickering flames. Rack is changed multiple times to avoid cross contamination of spices and seasonings. This a rare and unique Korean bbq service. Most restaurants use one bbq rack for the entire meal.

Unseasoned pork skirt meat cut into small bite sized strip and allowed to be cooked slowly, crisp but not burnt or dry within. Dip into awaiting hot Korean paste, salt, vinegar garlicky vegetable bath, or eat plain.

Pork belly strip sizzling to perfection. Scissor cut to bite sized nuggets to enhance cooking wait time. Plenty of other garnishes to sample while waiting. Also separate hot and cold soups served along with three banchans. The grill's molt contains minced kimchi and egg mixture plus there was a separate section for the creamy corn kernels.

Hand seared short rib sushi ... our server Nancy was in total control.  In fact between her and David, we just watched and enjoyed them diligently and skillfully grill our entire dinner.  So welcomed and different ... kinda get spoiled with such great wait service.
Triple tier meat serving stand.

You may select a beef combo, skirt steak combo, or a pork combo. We chose the pork combo. Combos are sized for 1-2 persons or 3-4 persons. Personally the 1-2 person could feed 3. At the end we had a lot of cooked meat to take home.
Heotkkae Berry Tea ... served chilled and no limits for refills. Beware that it really does work.

Community entrance and exit greeting. Try not to look startled. A bow is a friendly acknowledgement even if you don't understand a word of Korean. Seating capacity is for 175 persons. Parking could be problematic. The restaurant size, ambience and noise level can initially be over powering.

Skirt Meat Combo for four on a Monday evening. Table service second to none. Three of us could not finish the entire meal. For four diners, I would recommend the chicken to be included for extra $$. Banchan and salads were off the chart superb.

On my late night restaurant list. This time we tried their beef combo with the ribeye. Too much of a good thing is not good for Yu-go. Actually, we enjoyed the beef combo the most over the pork and skirt meat combos.

How it looks like on a Thursday 1 pm. Service is polite with just two dim sum carts roving around. They contain the dim sum staples. Anything requiring a griddle is via a visit to the food counter. Clean restrooms for a change.

Average dim sum dish $2.88. Favorites were har gow & shui mai. The cheung fun, fu jow, fried tofu stuffed with fishmeat were fair. Are they the best in the valley ?  Don't know. Since dim sum quality is like a bobbing target on a rapid flowing river in this valley. I like the concept and the venue ... can't quite bring it parallel with the present quality of the food.
This is the faucet that fills those tumblers ... a basin to wash those soiled hands.  Obviously the water is not filtered.
Normally we would consume 8 to 10 dishes. 5 was more than enough to evaluate the dim sum quality.
Tucked in the back corner of a 7-Eleven strip mall. Can't see the signage from Sunset or Arroyo Grande. Restaurant is very well lit exterior and interior.

Chicken Gyro ... moist chunks of grilled chicken with perfect mixture of cucumber, red onion, tomatoes, feta cheese & tzatziki sauce ... not to forget a couple of crispy fries.  Filling and perfectly satisfying.

Pork Gyro ... beautifully seasoned chunks of grilled pork. 1st pork gryo  ever for us. Upgraded to include soda and crispy fries. Was very impressed by the flavors, texture of pita bread and the value of the meal. Fries are exceptional... no need for ketchup.
Small Buffalo Chicken Pizza ... loaded with white chicken meat with hot sauce,  blue cheese & mozzarella.  Very hearty meal and plenty for two.
Akropolis fries with feta cheese, two wedges of lemon & tzatziki dip. Their crispy fries might just be the best in all of Henderson.

Traditional Greek Salad with fresh tomato wedges, sliced cucumbers,  large clumps of feta cheese, plenty of kalamata olives and thinly sliced red onions. You can eat the salad as is or add the homemade vinaigrette Greek dressing. It's an excellent meal in itself.

Had so much food, I decided to eat and share just one slice. The rest I took home and reheated @ 400¬∞ for ten minutes. Added garlic powder and chill flakes before baking. Talk about jackpot reward ... I'm still talking about it today.

Wednesday night we closed the restaurant with owners while viewing the Dubs playing the Lakers. Snacked on 12 fried chicken wings with hot sauce and blue cheese dressing on the side. It was chicken divine!

Gyro Salad with grilled pork ... not that blended lamb & beef concoction.  Romaine lettuce, tomatoes, kalmalta olives, red onion, feta cheese and Greek vinaigrette dressing. So refreshing and tasty. Heated top quality pita bread on the side. I normally don't eat the pita bread elsewhere because most of the time it's junk.
Working man's Italian hoagie. Ah, more than enough to feed the two of us.
Spanokopita dipped in tatziki ... crazy delicious!
Akropolis Large Pizza ....Cup & Char Pepperoni, Sausage, Hamburger,  Bacon , Mixed Peppers, added extra fresh garlic and requested it be baked extra crispy....more than a meal in itself for 4 of us.
Chicken gyro ... opa !
Starbucks Caesars Palace prices comes with the venue. My Strawberry Frappuccino was at least buck more ... still just as enjoyable
Starbucks Caesars Palace barista service was very polite and plenty of seating

Special Saturday promotion of       St. Louis style BBQ rack of pork ribs. Smoked early the same morning and ready by high noon. Each rack with ten ribs keeping the richly flavored moist tender pork meat together. ONE TASTE & Yu-go took two racks home with two pints of macaroni salad.  Ribs @ $15 with half for $8. Neatly all the other purchases were for the full rack.

All 500 lbs of meaty pork ribs smoked right in front the store. With the freshly BBQ'd meal in Yu-go's arms,  he had to defer visiting the store until the next trip.  BTW ... them ribs were incredibly irresistible and downright tasty. Can't wait for the next BBQ promotion!!
This St Louis style pork ribs experience has clobbered my recent Texas BBQ ribs. But the macaroni salad sealed the deal.  Tiny bits of pickled relish and celery  reminded us of what perfect meant.
Looking forward to the final weekend of October when lower temperatures will allow me to walk to my neighborhood grocery store.
Whole slab of BBQ St Louis style dry rubbed pork ribs. Big fan of Seasons bbqs.
Hot Dog Heaven ... at its finest moment.
Hell ya' Dirt Dog is the ultimate hot dog spot !!
Cyber Acoustics USB Stereo Headset w' Microphone for just $40 available at store. Plantronics was twice the price and not available at store.
3' USB 2.0 A to Micro-B priced $2.39 an unbeatable deal.
Camped out in Cafe 27 (store #27) with grande  ice Caraole French Dark Roasted coffee to keep the heart pumping ...  4\/5
Usually the best prices outside the internet
Ordered a Chamango, but on our receipt it's a Mangoneada Preperada.  Much different from the Mexican Chamango. Not as much mango but definitely sweeter with lots more chewy bits of candied plum.
Pollo, chorizo, lengua plus carnitas ... this will satisfy any hungry person.
Just pollo taco for me.  Most satisfying lunch. Can't wait to try other menu items.
On Tuesdays only,  it's pollo and chorizo tacos for just a $1 each.  Too good of a deal to not try.  Surprised by the quality and exceeded all expectations.
Painted art from prior ice cream operator.  Flowers close to ceiling are new
Yu-go's Chamango !   One scoop of Mango Sorbet and rest is fresh chunks of Mango. Prefer mango ice cream.
All sorts ice cream and sorbet flavors.
At corner of Eastern & Silverado behind  opposite corner of Windy City Hot Dogs & Pizza

Original" flavored "Raindrop"  Besides the clear giant gelatin drop, mix together the sweet and cocoa syrups and nut powder together and   scoop the mixture on to the raindrop.  All for a sweet fun new foodie experience.
Cotton Candy Shave ICE (lavender flavor)  Too good to be true.

Order at the counter and your deserts will be served at your table. Sorta of a one man show.  He was most helpful in our process of deciding  what to order.  Restrooms need lots more attention (imho) in comparison to sister restaurant Gnoog & Yuxiang.
This Halo Halo with flash freeze milk is the best I have ever tasted. Just ask all the angels who have passed through.
Very young crowd
No longer a hidden gem. When you're good, they'll find you.
Following our dinner Yu-go beelined  it to here and we ordered Halo-Halo .. it's so addictive.

Ordered following along with ratings: Santa Barbara Burger with swiss cheese plus extra mayo (4+); Teriyaki Burger (3, just okay);  crispy fries (2, didn't finish); onion rings (4+ with ranch dressing); & mocha shake (5). Decor (5)
Both California burger chains offer lettuce wrapped burgers. Quality of beef patties are near identical. They rank 4th and 5th on my fast food burger list.
Hulu Huli Chicken plus Korean Chicken Drummettes and wingettes plus Chicken Katsu
Called twice @ 5:45 pm and 5:48 pm to confirm they were open on 7\/22\/2017.  No one answered the phone. My food experience at their Eastern location was atrocious.

Certified Black Angus & Organic Grass Fed Beef 6oz burger.  Off the chart delish. The hand cut fries are free when you check in. Also ordered Onion Strings that were tasty when dipped in the ranch dressing.
Taking a break ... it's been a long day for us.
Bang  Bang Sliders ... pulled tender seasoned pork ...  legit tasty filling meal.
Drunken "AF" Rice Noodles ...  it's a noodle dish MOAB !  I'M HOOKED !
Dirty Chips ... nasty good stuff !
BIG WANG'" 4 whole chicken wings smothered  in sticky chili sweet sauce on top of a bed of partially seasoned white rice ... try not to eat your fingers too. LoL Great value plus very filling too.

BIG WANG" French- Vietnamese-Thai super sized banh mi sandwich. Comes with dipping sauce and extra garnishments to make it an exclusive tasty experience. Sandwich spread is a delicate not over powering sriracha-mayo.

Had to order it again the Drunken "AF" Noodles. Will have it later in the day. Registered for frequent dining program plus received a senior discount.  Great food along with enticing incentives. Happy Mother's Day !

No goat or lamb or heavy scent of cumin here. Wednesday night it's an 88% occidental audience watching the short guy on his tippy toes behind the counter hand making or slicing fresh made noodles. Ultra new, clean cut in every which way. For us Asians it's nice but we're here for the noodles and not the show. The seasoning is pampered to a foreign diner. IMHO

Three in our party which allows us to try many more dishes. I happened to order the soupless Tomato & Egg with hand-pulled noodles. In aggregate, it would be an obvious order revisited the next time. Why ?  Taste, seasoning, texture, and portion size. Good hearty meal.

Exceptionally lean pork belly hand-pulled noodle soup.  Next time Yu-go will ask for extra noodle plus heavier ammunition for chili sauce. You know the stuff that will eat through plastic containers and Chinese made vinegar. Next time he would prefer ordering the pork ribs which is seasoned and made in the same fashion. If it wasn't for the appetizers, he would have gone hungry after staring down this earthenware noodle bowl. (He calls it dumpster diving)

If Yu-go was a puppy, he would be in Chinese puppy happy hunting grounds. Stripping the tender pork meat from the tiny riblets adds to the gourmet experience. As for the chicken-pork broth ... an elixir that would cause the emperor chef to lose his head. It's tastier than a Styrofoam cup of instant noodles. Between the pork belly and ribs ... take the ribs for a more fulfilling meal.

Appetizers are in general very good. The Beef Pan Cakes are expertly fashioned to hold its juices just like a XLB.  Consistent flavor with a crispy crunch to each bite. Use the provided knife to halve the compact extra thick pancakes. Otherwise you will get an oil stain on your clothing. The accompanying dipping sauce was non-descripte and added nothing to the eating experience. Would definitely order this again and again.
Clever presentation of pork Pot Stickers. Accompanying sauce a non-factor. Skin is thin and contents finely combined.  I would not hesitate to order again.

Lightly seasoned and boiled cucumber topped with Mung Bean Sauce ... our first appetizer. Not aware if any other restaurant that prepares it in the same way. Unique and refreshing. Those seeking heavy vinegar seasoning will be sadly disappointed. Still worth trying IMHO.
Parking can be scarce on this hilly parking lot. If you can, carpool.
Having a facial...
Big promotion for cosmetics... never seen department so busy. Here for facials for Yu-go and myself.
Came by on a nice and quiet Sunday to pick up pre-sale Omorovizca skin care products
Spicy ahi with avocado plus spicy ahi furikake ... yummy yummy
Yu-go orders ahi sweet chili plus mayo ahi ... damn this is so good !
Taegu ...  save lots of money no having to fly to Costco on Oahu
It all looks so tasty ll
Been looking for a local Henderson Mexican grille that brings together good quality ethnic foods together with reasonable prices. I think Rivas Mexican Grill is now my first choice.
Legit Mexican foods at very reasonable prices. I shared a pastor nachos which was most delicious. Hope this tip doesn't get censored. Rivas is now my primary go to neighborhood Mexican food stop.
Pastor Nachos ... plenty enough to satisfy two of us. The pastor was very tasty and seasoned well enough to not require salsa. The corn nachos were really good.
Mac Salad just too sweet for liking.

Five chicken fingers with honey mustard dipping sauce for $7. It's all breast meat with flavorless batter. Well cooked and borderline dry.  I can see why my 6'4" 340 lbs pool boy raves about this snack shack. At 4:30 Saturday afternoon, it was a full house. Operated by different folks, the overall experience was very similar to the Sunset shack.
Our Saturday 2:30 pm lunch ... the food truly  exceeded our expectations. Every item is homemade. Lavash flat bread was a nice surprise. How about a strong 5 stars.
Grand Lula (Armenian kebab) was ordered takeout but the meal never left the Grand Kebab. LoL

Here's Chris the hard working owner of GRAND KEBAB.  We just finished trying his excellent Grand Lula and took home small side orders of Red Salad, Hummus & Tabbouleh. Restaurant is very contemporary, clean and relaxing with order counter and see through kitchen. Plenty of parking too.

Are you a Lamb Chops connoisseur ?  Look no further in Henderson or anywhere else in the Valley.  No where else will you find this quality serving at any price. Marinated in absolute Mediterranean  perfection.

I have an asbsolute affinity for pork chops. No matter the restaurant's ethnic specialty.  I purposely did not finish my meal so that I could savor these gems again the next day. Amazingly enjoyable for two meals.
Second time back within one week's time and without referencing  to the menu, we are going to order complete pork and lamb chops meals.
Chicken drumsticks meat peeled back before grilled.  Could be a favorite style.  Took home two for the extended holiday weekend.

Cornish hen ... extraordinarily large; Extraordinarily delicious too.  Been back multiple times in a week's time.  Ever since a local Greek restaurant changed hands, Mediterranean cuisine in Henderson has been nebulous until Grand Kebab.
First LAS NBA Summer League GSW v 76ers.  Ordered out and watching Game at Sunset Casino Sportsbook & Racing.
Graveyard special, oxtail soup, lots of meat, broth was lukewarm and had zero peanuts. This experience destroyed Yu-go's fond memories of the oxtail soup.
Hamburger Steak with brown, grilled onion, vegetables and rice.  Not to forget mac salad. Better of the two meals.

Seafood pancake with excellent dipping sauce; tofu surrounding kimchee pork belly; & cold plate noodle with dumpling.  Too much food but that's okay. Used pancake dipping sauce for the very plump meaty dumplings.  Also asked for vinegar for our lukewarm chewy noodles which surprised the young man who was our server. Dead giveaway to being Chinese. Would like to comeback to try more of their dishes and maybe meet "auntie".

Undeniably clean and neat. Sat close to the kitchen entryway with no hint of sweet pungent Korean cookery in the air ... amazing.   Contemporary Korean music in the background. Clean non-sticky table with service button and comfortable seats. Single sheet menu with illustrations of items on both sides accommodating first timers and non-Koreans. Ice cold water container with polished short metal tumblers. Good start

Just a few items we'll use in the next 8 days. Once upon a "Fresh & Easy" next door to Lucki Thai. Very well inventoried  especially seafood. Also glanced at their foodcourt"s PhilHouse. Magnolia ICE cream $3 off special or $3.99.
Lemongrass chicken spicy (?) ... someone forgot the chili sauce in the kitchen. Very plain until Yu-go jazzed it up. Included several slices  of cucumbers. A little expensive for $11.00.
Bun ... Noodles w\/o broth but with fish sauce.  Grilled pork plus tiny veggie rolls and shredded lettuce.  Stingy on mint and basil leaves. Otherwise, it was very good.

Clashing signals.  Playing two videos...one of beautiful VN and other American rap with sound to entertain employees . Our cute server with thick sweat pants torn way above the knee in 117¬∞ weather didn't speak a lick of VN nor understood menu items in VN. (I'm not VN) $25 for two very basic VN street food dishes is discouragingly expensive. Totally disagree with  the near 5 rating. More like half.
Beef Koobideh Kagan ... lunch $7.95.  Worth checking out.  Salad dressing red vinagerette  ... Yu-go loved it.  Great balanced meal.
Chicken Koobideh Kebab was grilled perfectly. Most enjoyable lunch combo.
Mast O Khiar ... Yogurt  with chopped cucumber, mint & herbs.  Used it on everything except as a facial cold cream.  LoL
Chopped the tomatoes as a topping for the rice. ... and salad is enough to fulfill a hungry appetite.
Split the beef and chicken Koobideh Kabobs between us.  They look and tasted so yummy.

There's two sides to this lunch menu. Plus the dinner menu is available.  Very large spacious and comfortable restaurant.  Next time we'll try the Cornish hen or lamb chops. Hopefully I will sit at a table far away from a loud diner without cell phone etiquette.
There's enough data on this receipt to trace the genetics of where my chicken breast originally  evolved from. ( Eh guys, Just kidding ).

Ordered a spicy sandwich meal along with their original sandwich which is a bare bun with chicken. Been over 8 years since my one and only visit to a CFA in Beltsville, MD. This visit reminded of why I hadn't returned in all those years. Love fried chicken legs, thighs & them wings,  but not the CFA style.

Waited for the grand opening and newness of this first NV franchise to simmer down. Even at 8:30 pm the chicken lovers kept showing up for more succulent breast meat. One has to ask where does the rest of the chicken parts wind up at.
Honey floating on Greek yogurt topped with fresh fruits.  One of my favorite desserts .
Village Salad without lettuce. So tasty and healthy.
Slow roasted lamb leg sandwich ... not to be ever ignored by any lamb meat lover.
Octopus exquisitely and perfectly prepared over white beans. A connoisseur's delight.

I'm with my very good friend Rosie.  We go back a lot of years, and it all started in Henderson. She's the sparkling "rose water" of this wonderful Greek restaurant. By good fortune Jerry and Harry were also on site too.
Chicken Thighs on a skewer with green salad ... insanely delicious !!
Fried calimari from Rhode Island. Tomato based sauce needed more pepper and salt.
Pork Pad Thai Lunch Special $7.50...expertly prepared and terrific value!
Minced Chicken w mint and steamed rice , lunch special $7.50...very satisfying
Spice on the side"  ordered everything at level 2 out of 5.  Just enough to know the heat is there.
Pad Woon Sen veggie. Exceptional !!!  Best in Vegas ...
Panang Curry Chicken  ... little too salty for us.  Made note of it to the server who passed it on to the chef. Otherwise it was very good.
Pork fried Egg Roll (5) came cucumber, lettuce, mint leaves with fish extract sauce.  A must try.
No outdoor signage yet.  Located between Subway & T-Mobile stores. Just outside of Home Depot. New operators are adding their personal touch with fresh coat of paint. Plenty of parking too.
Wednesday 1st cup on them for over age 50  Station Casino members.  Service has always been cordial.
My husband's favorite ... hand pulled noodle in black sauce along with raw white onions. Dreamy good. It's called J Jang Myeon.
Tang Su Yuk ... deep fried pork with sweet and slightly sour clear sauce.  Perfectly prepared in a perfect setting.
Seafood noodle soup.  Not over powering in spiciness and perfect for windy dry day.  It's  called J Jampong and is on every table.
My very good friend Todd S. says the cute creature is a "Tanuki" a racoon dog.

This is my third visit in less than 30 days (Not including stops at Omoide, Gnoog plus Loftti). My only complaint this time is that my two female servers never suggested refilling the two banchan dishes shared by three.  Also the kimchi was fragmented scraps as if it came from the bottom of the container. And, it would be nice if they had packaged the leftovers. After all this is not a food court concession.
Kkanpunggi .... deep fried chicken with garlic & chili ... delightfully satisfying !
Beef Tangsuyuk with sweet & sour sauce on the side. The best way to fully enjoy this dish.
Full order of Jjajangmyeon.  Noodles served mushy and cucumber portion as if for smaller order.  Didn't have enough white onion banchan. Room for improvement.
Waiting for a table.. the place looks like it was slammed on a Saturday night (4\/15\/17)
The menu gives you a lot of options for a complete meal.
It's freezing in here..good thing we had our jackets
Special Ohjah House Ramen ,add noodle. Perfect for sharing. The noodles are thick and chewy just the way we prefer. No dumpster diving required by Yu-go.
Appetizers...Fried Oysters with tonkatsu dipping sauce and Yaki Gyoza, both enjoyable.
Come after 9:00 pm if you don't want to wait.
Best tapa was the corn on the cob. Worst tapa was the unedible ultra salty octopus.
Best tapa was the Empanada. The sucky tapa was the Chicken Chiccarones.
Chef Lorena Garcia developed Chica's menu.  Unfortunately, the executive chef failed to execute and deliver. IMHO. What do I know i use to live in Miami, ha ha.
We were seated in the back and adjacent to the grill. Yu-go could not deal with the grill's exhaust.  Our server Myya was very cordial, but cannot say the same for her assistants.
The sunlight is brutal in the late afternoon. Especially for a store facing west. We went home to better enjoy our blueberry slush.
No shortage of table service for tonight. The $16.99 price for after 10 pm does not include premium meats.
Banchon 3\/5, meats 3+\/5, steam eggs and soup -4\/5, salad 4+\/5,  service 4+\/5
Half size order of meats is more than plenty for two people. In fact we ordered less than half of the available selections.
We smelled like a walking Korean bbq ... don't wear your Sunday's best.
This Korean AYCE provides and serves all the food at your table .Never have to leave your table.

This place was once a Hot Dog on a Stick franchise. Straight From Philly Steakout kept the fixtures intact.  It was freezing cold then and it's still freezing cold now. No more colorful hats and blouses and hotpants. The soft chewy buns are Amoroso's of Philadelphia.  The Phanatic sandwich with three melted cheeses and chili all over the tender beefshavings really did ring the bell for us.
Excellent value meaning it would take four tacos elsewhere to satisfy Yu-go's appetite.  Chicken meat was well seasoned and not just plain chopped ... more like sauteed !
For the price and quality ... this chicken burrito was impressive from the get go.
Starting from the left ... lengua, pollo and buche. Enough filling dropped onto the paper plate to make another taco serving.

JAVIER (mgr) is from So-Cal and very customer orientated.  Very pleasant hard working guy.  Place is just a month old.  Other two locations is Gardena & Lynnwood. Established in 1985. Front door is sticky ... pull on it harder. Very clean and relaxing. Restrooms are new and super clean. Ownership spent some serious $ to make you forget that this location was once a Jack in the Box.
Excellent strong flavors .... !!
Not very big but cleverly decorated ...
Pina Colada !!
Recent reviews have caused me to pause and remove my bookmark.
Could be the best fried chicken east of Interstate 15.  I'm serious.
Six pc chicken mix without rolls ... talk about bang for the bucks.
Good people with good fried chicken.
IMHO ... Undisputed king of fried chicken east of HWY 95

This is "Z'" who you order your fried chicken from. His uncle, Abdul works the kitchen. The fry cook is presumably a relative too. Family is in the restaurant business starting from New Jersey. Z told me that they are opening another location at 2797 Maryland Parkway, by Sunrise Hospital. Currently still under construction.
I am going to wait a few months to let this new place work our it's kinks.

Thank goodness, I'm seeing the box's bottom of a three month's supply of "San Francisco French Roast Gourmet Coffee".  The French "voila" reminisce of a weak cigarette after taste in the back of the mouth.
Fill up "Jiaozi" : odds and ends; plus a pizza extra crisp.
75 oz lattace apple pie fully baked for just $9.99.  Seems like every shopping cart had a pie. Parking lot was packed with cars waiting for an opening.

Shrimp Pad Thai & Crispy Duck Panang.  Good sized portions, spice level #4 mild. Enough to take some home for another meal with hot rice. Pack yourself  take home with anxious servers bussing dishes at the same time infuriated Yu-go. If you want the dishes so badly pack the food for me.

Beef Jerky; Grilled Beef Salad; Ginger Chicken; Drunken Noodle with shrimp wonton soup.  Slightly Americanized but our guest thought it was all superb ... which is all that matters.  Service was outstanding and no left overs.
Tom Yum Ka soup very mild in spiciness. Perhaps our favorite entree.  Our neighbors were pleasantly surprised and ate everything in sight.  Good for them.
What's left following piranha attack.  If you had Roti Roti, you will definitely enjoy their pork Rotisserie.  They also serve chicken and Beef tri tips.
Met co-owner Paul from SoCal.  Very personable and caring. So is his staff. Most important is their great food.
Perfect place for breakfast
Great local casino
Free cake and champagne until 8pm
Great food with an outstanding value
Love store and the prices BUT I hate the payment method
